#\#CIF_2.0
# Tests: value_type column in _cif_fallback reflects the lexer-assigned ValueType
# for each stored value. One example of each relevant ValueType is present:
#   STRING         -> bare word
#   PLACEHOLDER    -> unquoted . or ?
#   SINGLE_QUOTED  -> 'text'
#   DOUBLE_QUOTED  -> "text"
#   MULTILINE_STRING -> ;...;
# Triple-quoted types (CIF 2.0 only) are tested in the triple entry below.
# Dictionary: none (schema-less)

data_test_fallback_value_types
_t.string          bare_word
_t.placeholder_dot .
_t.placeholder_q   ?
_t.single_quoted   'hello world'
_t.double_quoted   "hello world"
_t.multiline
;line one
line two
;
_t.triple_single   '''triple single'''
_t.triple_double   """triple double"""
